 One-Line Exam Answer
The Bitcoin blockchain was created to enable secure, trustless peer-to-peer digital money and is practically used for payments, remittances, store of value, and data integrity beyond DeFi.

#II.Bitcoin Mining â€” Definition
Bitcoin mining is the process by which:
â€¢	New Bitcoin is created
â€¢	Transactions are verified and added to the blockchain
â€¢	Miners compete to solve complex cryptographic puzzles (Proof of Work) to add a new block to the Bitcoin blockchain. 
________________________________________
 2. Functions of Bitcoin Mining
ğŸ”¹ a. Transaction Verification
Miners check and validate transactions so the network stays secure and accurate. 
ğŸ”¹ b. Block Creation
Verified transactions are grouped into a block and added to the blockchain, forming a continuous, unalterable ledger. 
ğŸ”¹ c. Issuance of New BTC
Miners are rewarded with newly minted Bitcoin plus transaction fees for their work. 
ğŸ”¹ d. Network Security
By requiring Proof of Work to add blocks, mining makes it extremely hard to alter past transactions and prevents fraud or attacks. 
________________________________________
3. Bitcoin Mining â€” Process (Step-by-Step)
1.	Transaction Broadcast: Users send Bitcoin transactions to the network.
2.	Transaction Pool: Pending transactions enter the mempool waiting to be mined.
3.	Block Assembly: Miners group transactions into a candidate block.
4.	Proof of Work Puzzle: Miners repeatedly try different nonces to find a hash below the difficulty target.
5.	Block Found: The first miner to find a valid hash broadcasts the block.
6.	Verification & Addition: Other nodes verify the block and add it to the blockchain.
7.	Reward Distributed: Miner earns Bitcoin reward + fees. 
This Proof of Work (PoW) makes Bitcoin decentralized and secure by requiring computational effort. 
________________________________________
 4. Countries Involved in Bitcoin Mining (2026)
