â¡ï¸ These figures are based on industry surveys and hashrate data, showing how mining power is distributed globally. 
Additional Miners
Other countries with smaller shares include:
â€¢	Bhutan â€” mining with hydropower and holding significant BTC reserves. 
â€¢	Turkmenistan â€” recently established rules for mining and virtual assets. 
________________________________________
ğŸ“Œ Quick Summary (Exam-Ready)
Bitcoin mining is the process of validating transactions and adding them to the blockchain while minting new BTC. Miners compete in Proof of Work to secure the network. Its functions include transaction validation, block creation, and network security. Globally in 2026, major mining contributions come from the United States (~37.5 %), Russia (~16.4 %), China (~11.7 %), Canada (~7.1 %), and Kazakhstan/Paraguay (~3.4 %). 

#III.1. Global Blockchain Adoption by People
ğŸ“Œ User Base
In 2026, around 283 million people worldwide are actively using blockchain technology â€” representing about 3.9 % of the global population.

ğŸ“Œ Regional Adoption
Asia leads with the highest number of users (~160 million)
Europe and North America follow with millions more users
Usage in Oceania remains smaller (~1 million) compared with other regions.
This shows blockchain is still early in general population adoption, with under 4 % of people globally using it directly as of 2026.

2. Enterprise & Business Adoption
Business Engagement
